lar-anim.mp4" type=3D"video/mp4" data-filtered=3D"filtered"> Video tag is n=
ot supported.</video><i>Figure A: Circular object with a radiance probe.</i=
></div><p><em>Figure A</em>, depicts a <span class=3D"highlight">circular o=
bject</span> on the left, with a radiance probe to the right of it.<br data=
-filtered=3D"filtered"> The radiance probe has an angular resolution which =
can be defined as the angle between its evenly spaced rays. <em>(Shown in b=
lue)</em><br data-filtered=3D"filtered"> As the radiance probe moves <span =
class=3D"highlight">further away</span> from the light source, we can see t=
hat its <span class=3D"highlight">angular resolution</span> becomes insuffi=
cient.</p><p>What we can observe here is that the angle between rays we can=
