 have <span class=3D"highlight">equal the intervals</span>.</p><blockquote>=
<p>Meaning our total interval count will grow linearly with cascade count.<=
/p></blockquote><p>I <span class=3D"highlight">recommend</span> using the <=
strong>4x</strong> branching method where interval count remains equal, it =
is <span class=3D"highlight">simpler</span> to work with in practice.</p><h=
3 id=3D"cascade-gathering">Cascade Gathering</h3><p>To gather the <span cla=
ss=3D"highlight">radiance</span> for each cascade we simply loop over each =
texel in its memory texture.<br data-filtered=3D"filtered"> For each of tho=
se texels we <em>calculate the direction</em> and cast our interval into th=
e scene.</p><p>First, let's find out what our coordinate is within the prob=
