ow merged all the cascades down into <strong>cascade0</strong>.</p><h3 id=
=3D"final-pass">Final Pass</h3><p>I did say <em>"that's all"</em>, I know, =
I know, but there's <span class=3D"highlight">one more step</span>,<br data=
-filtered=3D"filtered"> which is to <span class=3D"highlight">integrate</sp=
an> the irradiance stored in the now merged <strong>cascade0</strong>.</p><=
p>Luckily this is <em>relatively trivial</em>, we already have most of the =
code we need.<br data-filtered=3D"filtered"> We simply <span class=3D"highl=
ight">bilinearly interpolate</span> between the <strong>4</strong> nearest =
<strong>cascade0</strong> probes for each pixel.<br data-filtered=3D"filter=
ed"> And sum up the radiance from all intervals. <em>(cones)</em></p><div c=
lass=3D"img"><img alt=3D"Figure P: Final result! (Credit: Fad's Shadertoy)"=
 title=3D"Figure P: Final result! (Credit: Fad's Shadertoy)" src=3D"https:/=
