Figure P: Final result! (Credit: Fad's Shadertoy)</i></div><blockquote><p>I=
mage credit: <a href=3D"https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mtlBzX">Fad's Shader=
toy</a>.</p></blockquote><p>If we did everything correctly, we should end u=
p with a <span class=3D"highlight">beautiful</span> result like in <em>Figu=
re P</em>.</p><p>For those who made it all the way till the end, <span clas=
s=3D"highlight">thank you</span> for reading my article!<br data-filtered=
=3D"filtered"> I hope it sheds some light on how &amp; why <span class=3D"h=
ighlight">Radiance Cascades</span> work.<br data-filtered=3D"filtered"> It =
took me a while to properly understand it, and a lot of trial &amp; error t=
o get it working :)</p><hr><h2 id=3D"amazing-resources">Amazing Resources</=
h2><p>There's quite a few resources already out there related to RC. <em>(w=
hich also helped me)</em><br data-filtered=3D"filtered"> I will list a few =
of them here, so you can get explanations from <span class=3D"highlight">di=
fferent perspectives</span>:</p><ul><li>Alexander Sannikov's <a href=3D"htt=
ps://github.com/Raikiri/RadianceCascadesPaper">paper</a> on Radiance Cascad=
es.</li><li>XorDev &amp; Yaazarai's articles, <a href=3D"https://mini.gmsha=
ders.com/p/radiance-cascades">part 1</a> &amp; <a href=3D"https://mini.gmsh=
aders.com/p/radiance-cascades2">part 2</a>.</li><li>SimonDev's video <a hre=
f=3D"https://youtu.be/3so7xdZHKxw">https://youtu.be/3so7xdZHKxw</a>.</li><l=
i>Christopher M. J. Osborne's <a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.14425">=
paper</a> diving deeper into the bilinear fix.</li><li>Jason's blog post <a=
 href=3D"https://jason.today/rc">https://jason.today/rc</a>.</li><li>Fad's =
<a href=3D"https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mtlBzX">Shadertoy</a> implementat=
ion.</li></ul><blockquote><p>Also check out our <a href=3D"https://discord.=
